<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298390>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 116. Metasomal sterna, ♂. A. Lasioglossum (D.) zephyrus (Smith, 1853), with hair concentrated in apicolateral areas of S3–5. B. Typical red-tailed Lasioglossum (Dialictus), with hair evenly distributed and S5 straight. C. L. (D.) hudsoniellum (Cockerell, 1919), with S5 concave." ;
